  "texts": [
    "As for the clique counting or self-avoiding path counting problems in [CGV25], relying on R ij alone together with a Markov type bound is not sufficient.",
    "For this reason, we rely again on a Median-of-Means post-processing and we use the same notation as in the latter.",
    "In particular, we fix Λ = 24 log(n) and we assume for simplicity that (n -2)/Λ is an integer.",
    "Recall the definition of N = (n -2)/Λ + 2 and let J (1),.",
    ", J (Λ) be a partition of [n] \\ {i, j} into L disjoint parts."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "As for the clique counting or self-avoiding path counting problems in [CGV25], relying on R ij alone together with a Markov type bound is not sufficient."
  ]
}